I’m not sure how 4 years has come and gone, but here we are! 4 years since the day I became a mama, on Mother’s Day. We could not have been blessed with a more special little person to call ours. Luke is brilliant, way too witty for a toddler, observant af (kid doesn’t miss a THING), talkative unless you really want to know something 😂, creative and loving all things art, naturally athletic and can run about as fast as me 😳, funny, adorable, and sweet. He is a contrarian, so you can expect to be wrong even when you’re right. He knows exactly how to drive you mad, but if you can laugh it off, you will get along just fine. 🫠 He doesn’t just keep us on our toes. He exhausts us until our bones hurt, and he is ready to shoot out of bed and hit the ground running at 5:30am every single day. There are no words to express the depth of our adoration and love for our first baby who is now A FOUR YEAR OLD. Happiest birthday to our Lukey! ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🌈🍃
The 90-second cut of 365 days of my sweet boy for his 4th trip around the sun. 💙 Happy birthday, my Lukey!
365 days of our sweet boy for his 4th trip around the sun. Happy birthday, Lukey! 🩵

When I first found out I was pregnant with our 2nd, I wanted another boy. I was obsessed with our son. I knew what to expect. I wanted him to have a built in best friend. As the brute force of the 1st trimester nausea hit me, I knew deep down it was a girl. When Luke popped the balloon, sure as shit, pink confetti came raining down. In hindsight, I think I was just terrified of my role as the mother of a female that will inevitably go through all of the trials and tribulations that being a female lends itself, as I reflected on the 35 years’ worth of them in my own life. Now, I think it’s fairly silly to have a gender preference. The universe perfectly crafted this little being from an endless array of magical star dust, and we have the distinct privilege of calling her ours. And she is exactly who she is supposed to be. And we are doing everything we can to keep her that way. And as long as we are working overtime to encourage her to be true to herself, I do believe the rest will fall into place, just as it should. Just like the star dust that created her. 💫💛✨

These pictures portray my beautiful little girl in dresses and frills, but make no mistake, she fills the bottom of the tub with dirt every night. Her clothes are all stained. Her skin is kissed by the sun. She likes to play with rocks and mulch and leaves and monster trucks and balls. She is my little wild thing. My perfectly beautiful, dirty, sweaty, sweet as sugar little child of the earth. 🤎🌎

📷: @christinalouisephotos

social_posts.post_text:
Thanksgiving day 2023. 💛

Ever since we had Luke, we hosted thanksgiving for our families at our house to avoid a busy day of bouncing from dinner to dinner as we had for the 8 years prior. This would have been year 5, and we decided we needed a break from it. So we went on a little mountain escape for the week, and this was how we spent the better part of our day, in our favorite place, reveling in our kids being able to experience a level of freedom we can’t quite give them at home.

On a day intended for gratitude, I can say with conviction that I felt my cup overflowing with it by day’s end. The perfect day. 🥹
